<i>noun</i>: 어른 [어ː른], 성인 [성인], 대인 [대ː인] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>어른 [어ː른]</dt><br>
<dd>1. adult</dd><br>
<dd>다 자란 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A fully-grown person.</dd><br>
<dd>2. elder</dd><br>
<dd>나이나 지위 등이 높은 윗사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who is superior in age, position, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. grown-up</dd><br>
<dd>결혼을 한 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A married person.</dd><br>
<dd>4. elder</dd><br>
<dd>한 집안이나 집단 등에서 나이가 많고 경험이 많아 남에게 존경을 받는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person in the family or group who is respected by others because of his old age and experience.</dd><br>
<dd>5. father</dd><br>
<dd>(높이는 말로) 남의 아버지.</dd><br>
<dd>(polite form) The father of someone else.</dd><br>
<dt>성인 [성인]</dt><br>
<dd>adult; grown-up</dd><br>
<dd>어른이 된 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who is an adult.</dd><br>
<dt>대인 [대ː인]</dt><br>
<dd>1. adult</dd><br>
<dd>자라서 어른이 된 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who has grown up to become an adult.</dd><br>
<dd>2. man of virtue; noble man</dd><br>
<dd>말과 행동이 바르고 점잖으며 인격이 높은 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who speaks and behaves politely and decently, and has a noble personality.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>